The paper deals with detecting fraudulent entities in multimodal data, which involves modeling a tensor into a weighted graph and finding dense subgraphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Among these, cs.SI and cs.DS are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the main focus of the paper.
